        <updateDate>2017-12-15T14:13:36Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Settlement Tax Deductions are Over for Predators Act or the STOP Act </b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to deny a trade or business expense deduction for any amount paid or incurred on account of a judgment or settlement originating from, or to require the non-disclosure of or otherwise prevent, a claim or accusation of sexual abuse or sexual harassment (including unwelcome sexual advances, requests for sexual favors, or other verbal or physical harassment of a sexual nature).</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
